<item>
            <title>[HBASE-16203] may be a bug on hbase authorization</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16203</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in hbase with kerbose and authorization on, I enter hbase shell with a hbase super user, and do the following steps:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. grant  &quot;newUser/slave2@HADOOP.COM&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;newUser/slave2@HADOOP.COM&quot; is one of the kerbose principles&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. exit hbase shell&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. enter hbase shell again with principle &quot;newUser/slave2@HADOOP.COM&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4. scan &apos;t1&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
t1 is one of the table in hbase&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the result is: AccessDeniedException &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;after debug regionServer code, I find the problem is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. when we grant the global admin to &quot;newUser/slave2@HADOOP.COM&quot;, TableAuthManager store this info with the whole name, newUser/slave2@HADOOP.COM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. when we enter hbase shell with principle &quot;newUser/slave2@HADOOP.COM&quot; and scan table, regionServer will do do authorization check, such as check if the user is superUser&lt;br/&gt;
when do this check, use the short name(newUser), not the whole name(newUser/slave2@HADOOP.COM)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
</description>
