i think if we use hbase authorization, will must meet this problem &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15381524" author="enis" created="Sun, 17 Jul 2016 21:20:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you please ask the question user@hbase.apache.org or dev@hbase.apache.org.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In short, you should give authorization to a principal (like newUser), rather than an instance of the principle, like &quot;newUser/hostname@DOMAIN&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
